<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-974-662  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 974 662.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Dec 11 1989 n568 p89(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Pacts push Looking Glass interface. (Visix Software's OEM pacts)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ryan, Margaret.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Visix Software Inc has signed additional contracts in its effortto promote its Looking Glass graphical user interface as a Unixstandard.andP;  Looking Glass was introduced at the November 1989 UnixExpo in New York and has had a fast-paced acceptance in the Unixmarket.andP;  More than $35 million in OEM contracts have already beenannounced for the interface.andP;  However, some analysts fear that the$595 to $795 price per copy could prevent it from challengingMotif from the Open Software Foundation and other Unix graphicaluser interfaces.andP;  Analysts say an interface must be low-priced tocover a broad range of the market, like the $200 to $250 averageprice of an IBM PC graphical user interface.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Visix Software Inc. (contracts).andO;Product:   Looking Glass (Graphical user interface) (contracts).andO;Topic:     Graphical User InterfaceUNIXOEMsStandardizationCompetitionCost Benefit Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>